oracle.wsc.android.call

Class Call

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.wsc.android.session.SubSession
      • oracle.wsc.android.call.Call

  • public class Call
extends SubSession
    Represents a call which could have any combination of audio/video/dataChannel capabilities.

    The capability of a Call is determined when it is created. This capability is configured in the CallConfig object and input as the second parameter in CallPackage.createCall(java.lang.String).

      • accept

        public void accept(CallConfig config,
                   org.webrtc.MediaStream[] localStreams)
            throws IllegalArgumentException
        Accepts the received Call invitation.
        Parameters:
        config - Local capability configuration of the Call.

        This callConfig must not conflict with rules of RFC 3264. For example, if the callConfig of call.onIncomingCall or call.onUpdate is (SENDONLY, NONE), this callConfig cannot be (SENDONLY, NONE), but it can be (RECVONLY, NONE) or (NONE, NONE).

        localStreams - pre-created local media streams array
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - thrown if no local streams were created

      • accept

        public void accept(CallConfig config,
                   Map extHeaders,
                   org.webrtc.MediaStream[] localStreams)
            throws IllegalArgumentException
        Accepts the received Call invitation.
        Parameters:
        config - Local capability configuration of the Call.

        This callConfig must not conflict with rules of RFC 3264. For example, if callConfig of call.onIncomingCall or call.onUpdate is (SENDONLY, NONE), this callConfig cannot be (SENDONLY, NONE), but it can be (RECVONLY, NONE) or (NONE, NONE).

        extHeaders - extension headers. If provided, they are inserted into the JSON message.

        For example an extHeaders formatted like this, {'customerKey1':'value1','customerKey2':'value2'}
        will be in the message formatted like this :
        { "control" : {}, "header" : {...,'customerKey1':'value1','customerKey2':'value2'}, "payload" : {}}

        localStreams - pre-created local media streams array
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - thrown if no local streams were created

      • decline

        public void decline(int code)
        Decline the call with a reason code. The default value is 603 decline.
        The available reason codes are:
        • 486: busy here
        • 603: decline
        • 600: busy everywhere
        Parameters:
        code - code The decline code reason

      • decline

        public void decline(int code,
                    Map extHeaders)
        Decline the call with a reason code. The default value is 603 decline.
        The available reason codes are:
        • 486: busy here
        • 603: decline
        • 600: busy everywhere
        Parameters:
        code - code The decline code reason
        extHeaders - extension headers. If provided, they are inserted into the JSON message.
        For example an extHeaders formatted like this, {'customerKey1':'value1','customerKey2':'value2'}
        will be in the message formatted like this :
        { "control" : {}, "header" : {...,'customerKey1':'value1','customerKey2':'value2'}, "payload" : {}}
